This recipe was easy to make and tasted better the next day. I used boneless short ribs and veal broth instead of the beef broth, and I cooked the ribs for a total of 4 1/2 hrs (2.5 hrs the first night, 2 hrs the second). I added the olives prior to cooking the ribs the second night, which gave the ribs much of its saltiness. I also removed about 1/2 of the cooked broth/gravy from the pan, added a bit more salt, and reduced it for about 45 minutes prior to serving. I'd definitely make this again for a dinner party, as it's easy to prepare ahead and reheat the next day.

