Rating: 4
I've been making this dish as one of our favorite comfort stews since it first appeared several years ago, but prefer using a 4-lb chuck roast which I cut into 12-16 very large chunks, each approximating the size of a short rib. Less fat, less waste, more meat, and more economical. I also eliminate the extra 1/2 cup of water, and use pitted Kalamata olives. Go easy on the salt, as the olives provide much of the saltiness in the dish, and definitely do reduce the sauce down after removing the solids. One of my favorite tricks during that last stage is to add a tbsp or so of honey - it adds a glossiness to the sauce, and helps cut the acidity from the tomatoes. Just had this again last night and it continues to delight.

